title: Master of War [3-4] - David Gilman
description:
Gate of the Dead

   Tuscany, 1358: 

Thomas Blackstone has built a formidable reputation in exile, fighting as a mercenary amid the ceaseless warring of Italy’s City States. But when a dying man delivers a message recalling him to England, it seems to be a trap. 

Yet Blackstone cannot disobey and will brave the terrors of the High Alps in winter, face the Black Prince in tournament and submit to trial by combat. 

Every step of the way, he is shadowed by a notorious assassin with orders to dispatch him


     Viper's Blood

   England, 1346: 

For Thomas Blackstone the choice is easy... dance on the end of a rope for a murder he did not commit, or join the king’s invasion. 

As he fights his way across Northern France, Blackstone learns the brutal lessons of war.


Vastly outnumbered, Edward III’s army will finally confront the armoured might of the French nobility on the field of Crécy. It is a battle that will change the history of warfare.


Narrated By: Colin Mace

Format: Stereo mp3

Bit Rate: 64Kbps/44.1Hz
